This paper deals with the state complexity of various types of quantum finite automata and their relationships with other complexity classes. This topic falls under the area of computational complexity theory, which is covered by cs.CC. The paper also discusses quantum logarithmic space computation, which is a subfield of quantum computing and falls under cs.QL. The study of finite automata and their state complexity is closely related to the study of data structures, which is covered by cs.DS. The paper also discusses parameterized complexity, which is covered by cs.LO. Finally, the paper uses information theory to analyze the size of descriptions of automata, which is covered by cs.IT.
